        <div class="first-main">
        
  
    <p>
      Welcome to the Tanikala Voting System, the official blockchain-based voting platform for the student government elections at Bulacan State University. Below, you will find descriptions of each tab and contact information for support.
    </p>
    <br />
    <br />
    <h1 class="center">Tab Descriptions</h1>

  <div class="indent">
    <ul class="tabs">
      <li>
        <h3>Dashboard</h3>
        <p>
          Provides quick access to essential election-related information, including voter details, candidates, election results, and blockchain statistics such as the current admin fund, total blockchain expenses, registered voters, and voter turnout.
        </p>
      </li>
      <br />
      <li>
        <h3>Configuration</h3>
        <p>
          Allows administrators to configure election details, including the election name, registration period, voting period, party lists, and the list of colleges along with their student population.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
      <li>
        <h3>Candidate Management</h3>
        <p>
          Enables the addition, modification, and removal of candidates participating in the election.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
      <li>
        <h3>Blockchain Management</h3>
        <p>
          Displays blockchain-related information, including admin wallet details, blockchain transactions, and other relevant blockchain data.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
      <li>
        <h3>Blockchain Activity Log</h3>
        <p>
          Records all blockchain-related activities, ensuring transparency and accountability in blockchain operations.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
      <li>
        <h3>Voter Information</h3>
        <p>
          Provides a list of registered voters, including their status and other relevant details.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
      <li>
        <h3>Voter Turnout</h3>
        <p>
          Monitors and tracks voter participation in real-time during the election period.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
      <li>
        <h3>Vote Tally</h3>
        <p>
          Displays vote counts per candidate as the election progresses.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
      <li>
        <h3>Election Results</h3>
        <p>
          Presents the final results of the election once voting has concluded.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
      <li>
        <h3>Reset Election</h3>
        <p>
          Allows administrators to reset the election data in case of an official restart.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
      <li>
        <h3>Election Archives</h3>
        <p>
          Stores past election data for reference and record-keeping.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
      <li>
        <h3>Edit Account</h3>
        <p>
          Enables administrators to update their account details and credentials.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
      <li>
        <h3>Manage Admins</h3>
        <p>
          Allows for the addition and removal of admin accounts responsible for overseeing the election process.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
      <li>
        <h3>Help Page</h3>
        <p>
          Provides information on how to use the system, including FAQs and support contacts.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
      <li>
        <h3>System Activity Log</h3>
        <p>
          Logs all administrative activities within the system for security and auditing purposes.
        </p>
      </li>
       <br />
    </ul>
    </div>
